Record Class InputDialogPane.ButtonDef<R>

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
com.dua3.utility.fx.controls.InputDialogPane.ButtonDef<R>
Type Parameters:
R - the result type associated with the dialog
Record Components:
type - the ButtonType representing the type of the button
resultHandler - a DialogPaneBuilder.ResultHandler to handle the result when the button is pressed
action - a Consumer that specifies the action to be executed when the button is clicked
enabled - a BooleanExpression indicating whether the button is enabled or disabled
Enclosing class:
InputDialogPane<R>
public static record InputDialogPane.ButtonDef<R>(javafx.scene.control.ButtonType type, DialogPaneBuilder.ResultHandler<R> resultHandler, Consumer<InputDialogPane<R>> action, javafx.beans.binding.BooleanExpression enabled) extends Record
Represents the definition of a button in an InputDialogPane. This class encapsulates the details required to configure a button, including its type, associated action, result handler, and enablement state.

  • Method Details

    • cancel

      public static <Q> InputDialogPane.ButtonDef<Q> cancel()
      Creates and returns a ButtonDef instance configured as a cancel button. The cancel button is defined with a ButtonType.CANCEL, a result handler that always returns true, an action that performs no operation, and an enablement state that is always true.
      Type Parameters:
      Q - the type of the result associated with this button
      Returns:
      a ButtonDef instance representing a cancel button

    • create

      public static <Q> InputDialogPane.ButtonDef<Q> create(javafx.scene.control.ButtonType type, DialogPaneBuilder.ResultHandler<Q> resultHandler, Consumer<InputDialogPane<Q>> action, javafx.beans.binding.BooleanExpression enabled)
      Creates a new ButtonDef instance with the specified parameters.
      Type Parameters:
      Q - the type of the result associated with the button
      Parameters:
      type - the ButtonType representing the type of the button (e.g., OK, CANCEL, etc.)
      resultHandler - a DialogPaneBuilder.ResultHandler to handle the result when the button is pressed
      action - a Consumer specifying the operation to execute when the button is clicked
      enabled - a BooleanExpression that determines whether the button is enabled or disabled
      Returns:
      a new ButtonDef instance configured with the provided parameters
